#Text=The Denver Nuggets ( 23 - 41 ) defeated the New York Knicks ( 12 - 50 ) 106 - 78 on Monday at the Pepsi Center in Denver .
#Text=After an even first quarter , the Nuggets got hot in the second , out - scoring the Knicks 30 - 15 to go into the half up by 15 .
#Text=They continued with that momentum in the third quarter , this time out - scoring the Knicks 36 - 19 .
#Text=With such a large lead following the third , the Nuggets were then able to coast to the easy victory in front of their home crowd in the fourth .
#Text=They were the superior shooters in this one as well , finishing at 44 percent from the field , while the Knicks went just 39 percent .
#Text=They also forced the Knicks into 14 turnovers , while committing just eight of their own .
#Text=Kenneth Faried got the start at center in this matchup , as Jusuf Nurkic was sitting out as he nursed an ankle injury .
#Text=Despite being undersized for the center position , he went off for a team - high of 19 points ( 7 - 12 FG , 5 - 7 FT ) , while also adding 11 rebounds and a blocked shot in just 27 minutes .
#Text=After struggling for a good portion of the season , he 's started to pick things up lately , posting four double - doubles over his last five games .
#Text=During that five - game stretch , he 's averaging 15 points and 12 rebounds .
#Text=Wilson Chandler also played well .
#Text=He went 6 - for - 10 from the field and 2 - for - 4 from the three - point line for 17 points , to go along with six rebounds in 23 minutes .
#Text=He could 've had more , but he was rested with the Nuggets having such a big lead .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Will Barton continued his surprising play with the Nuggets and posted 17 points ( 6 - 13 FG , 0 - 3 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) , four rebounds and three assists .
#Text=Since coming over to the Nuggets from the Portland Trail Blazers 10 games ago , he 's averaged 14 points , 4 rebounds , 2 assists and 1 steals per game .
#Text=Ty Lawson was the other Nugget in double figures , as he finished with 14 points ( 3 - 6 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 7 - 9 FT ) and six assists .
#Text=For the Knicks , Alexey Shved was in the starting lineup at shooting guard with Tim Hardaway Jr out with a back injury .
#Text=Shved made the start count , finishing with a team - high of 19 points ( 6 - 12 FG , 3 - 6 3Pt , 4 - 6 FT ) in just 25 minutes .
#Text=It was his second strong performance in a row , as he just posted 15 points against the Pacers on Saturday .
#Text=Considering he 's averaged just 9 points so far this season , he 's been a nice surprise for the Knicks since coming over from the Rockets in February .
#Text=Langston Galloway was another player who had a decent showing Monday .
#Text=He went 7 - for - 9 from the field to score 14 points , to go along with three rebounds and four assists .
#Text=He continues to be very inconsistent for the Knicks , as his scoring and rebounding numbers fluctuate at a high rate from game to game .
#Text=Andrea Bargnani had been turning some heads recently with two games in a row scoring more than 20 points .
#Text=He came back down to earth a bit Monday and finished with just 12 points ( 4 - 14 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 3 - 4 FT ) and seven rebounds .
#Text=To be fair , he did play just 24 minutes due to the nature of the blowout , so he probably would have put up some some higher point totals with more time on the court .
#Text=The Nuggets ' next game will be at home against the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday , while the Knicks will travel to Utah to play the Jazz on Tuesday .
